          <article id="crowdsourced-stories" class="source-article">
            <header>
              <h2>Crowdsourced stories</h2>
              <h3>Crowdsourced stories are submitted by GFW users to report what is happening in forest on the ground</h3>
              <%= link_to 'Submit your story', new_story_path, :class => "btn green medium uppercase"%>
            </header>
            <div class="content">
              <div id="storiesKeepView" class="stories-box">
                <ul>
                  <% @visible.each do |story| %>
                    <li>
                      <a href="<%= story_path(story['id']) %>">
                        <figure><div class="bg" style="background-image: url(<%= story_image_or_map(story['media'], "#{story['lat']}, #{story['lng']}") %>)"></div></figure>
                        <article class="info">
                          <h4><%= story['title'] %></h4>
                          <p><%= truncate(story['details'], :length => 295) %></p>
                          <button class="btn gray medium">More</button>
                        </article>
                      </a>
                    </li>
                  <% end %>
                </ul>
                <div class="section-footer">
                  <div id="pagination-container" data-page="<%= @page %>" data-perpage="<%= @stories_per_page %>" data-total="<%= @total_stories %>"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article id="monitor-an-area-of-interest" class="source-article">
            <header>
              <h2>Monitor an area of interest</h2>
              <p>Sign up to receive tree clearing alerts for the humid tropical forest biome. Tree clearing alerts indicate areas where tree cover loss is likely to have recently occurred, based off of an analysis of satellite imagery and complimentary data on forest fires and weather events. To learn more about this data set and where it applies, please visit the data page.</p>
              <p>When you sign up to receive alerts for an area of interest, you will be notified when a new tree clearing has been detected, as often as every 30 days. Once you identify the area you would like to monitor, simply enter your email address to subscribe to alerts.</p>
              <p>Choose a subscription option below.</p>
            </header>
            <div class="content">
              <ul class="alert-list">
                <li>
                  <h3>Subscribe to alerts for a hand-drawn area on the map</h3>
                  <p>Click the button below to enter the map with the analysis tool activated. Simply draw a shape within the humid tropical forest biome (the area shaded in pink) and click “Analyze.” Once the results appear, click the “mail” icon on the bottom of the analysis window. Enter your email address to subscribe.</p>
                  <a href="/map/3/15.00/27.00/ALL/grayscale/forma?begin=2006-01-01&end=2014-10-31" class="btn light2 medium uppercase">Draw an area</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <h3>Subscribe to alerts for a land use concession or protected area.</h3>
                  <p>Click the button below to enter the global map. Simply turn on a land use concession (logging, mining, oil palm, or wood fiber) or protected area layer and click on the individual concession or protected area you would like to analyze. When the information window pops open, click the “analyze” icon. Once the results appear, click the “mail” icon on the bottom of the analysis window. Enter your email address to subscribe.</p>
                  <a href="/map/3/15.00/27.00/ALL/grayscale/forma?begin=2006-01-01&end=2014-10-31" class="btn light2 medium uppercase">Select a concession or protected area</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <h3>Subscribe to alerts in a country or subnational region.</h3>
                  <p>Click the button below to access the country profiles, where you can select your country of interest. Within a country profile, you can select a subnational region using the dropdown menu under the country name. Once you define your area of interest (country or subnational region), click “Analyze on map.” You will then be directed to the map to perform an analysis. Once the results appear, click the “mail” icon on the bottom of the analysis window. Enter your email address to subscribe.</p>
                  <a href="/countries" class="btn light2 medium uppercase">Select a country or subnational region</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </article>
